"I'm a freelance product designer negotiating a contract for a product redesign. My standard rate is $120/hr but I'd accept $90/hr for the right engagement — I told the client my floor is $110. I'm between contracts and my runway is about 6 weeks before I have to take whatever comes along. I'd prefer a longer commitment (3+ months guaranteed) over a higher hourly rate since stability matters more right now. The client's product would be a strong portfolio piece and I don't want to price myself out. I'm worried that dropping my rate too much would make the client see me as junior talent and micromanage the project."
